item.title: Final
item.description: Free Response Final Review # Classes # Stacks # Stacks are a commonly used data structure in computer science, and especially for memory: Quite complicated. However, the foundation of stacks is quite simple. Just think of ‘em as pancakes! If you wanted to add to a stack, where would you add it to? Well, of course the top, since it’d be a hastle and borderline dangerous to your breakfast to lift up a bunch of pancakes for no reason.
